  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the stories, then, were changing, you know, from Hitler invading to what we're going to do and how we should have done it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, it's, it's here, and, and now what do we do?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what's going to happen tomorrow?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was no longer next week or what should we have done a year ago?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now we're confronted with the devil himself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and no matter how I imagine how badly they-- anyone perceived what was going to happen, it turned out infinitely greater, so that we were instantly cut off from everything, and the instant brutality, the instant orders, the instant change was not a, a slower way of introducing you into that kind of existence.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like the door shutting on you, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the separation from the Gentile area to the Jewish quarters was almost instantaneous.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The separation of building, building fences and building-- virtually building fences up and down streets in the ghetto to separate you from the Gentile versus the Jewish quarters, the building of bridges where you had to cross streets.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- we were-- the-- we, we would-- had to build these humongous bridges to cross over to-- the ghetto was, like, comprised of-- if this was a main street, they would build-- they would build fences on both sides of the streets.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the middle would be for the military or for streetcars or transportation.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on each side, the Jews resided.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
